levision industries. Divided into three main sections on ‘History and Spaces of Resistance’, ‘The Personal Experience’ and ‘Displacement, Participation and Spectatorship’, Post-1990 Documentary: Reconfiguring Independence provides an innovative interpretation of under-studied subject matters and styles, and rare analysis of differing production, distribution and exhibition strategies. It not only helps to rethink the notion of independence, but also contributes to a fundamental change in our perception of documentary filmmaking.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aDocumentary filmsxHistory and criticism. 4aFilm, Media & Cultural Studies. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / Direction & Production.2bisacsh1 aBroderick, Mick, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aByg, Barton, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChung, Hilary, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDeprez, Camille, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFeigelson, Kristian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGalmard, Eric, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGoursat, Juliette, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHughes, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIngham, Mike, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJacobs, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLuciano, Bernadette, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMaasdorp, Liani, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMorag, Raya, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPernin, Judith, eauthor.4aut4http